ite-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B10S1.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B10S1.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>14 days or More</td><td>The client has had difficulty breathing for 14 days or more</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B11S1.DE03<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B11S1.46DE03\"> </a></td><td>Less than 14 days</td><td>The client has had diarrhoea for less than 14 days</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B11S1.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B11S1.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>14 days or More</td><td>The client has had diarrhoea for 14 days or more</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>Less than 7 days</td><td>The client has had fever for less than 7 days</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE05<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE05\"> </a></td><td>7 Days or more</td><td>The client has had fever for 7 days or more</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">joint_pain<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-joint_pain\"> </a></td><td>Joint or Bone Pain</td><td>The client is reported to have or has had joint or bone pain</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE09<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE09\"> </a></td><td>Pain or Difficulty Passing Urine or Crying when Passing Urine</td><td>The client is reported to have or has had pain or difficulty passing urine or crying when passing urine</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE10<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE10\"> </a></td><td>Skin Problem</td><td>The client is reported to have or is observed to have skin pain or problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE11<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE11\"> </a></td><td>Ear Pain</td><td>The client is reported to have or has had ear pain</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE12<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE12\"> </a></td><td>Other</td><td>The client is reported to have or has had another type of pain</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">no_pain<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-no_pain\"> </a></td><td>No Pain</td><td>The client is reported to have no pain</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE14<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE14\"> </a></td><td>High Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a high malaria risk area</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE15<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE15\"> </a></td><td>Low Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a low malaria risk area</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B12S1.DE16<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B12S1.46DE16\"> </a></td><td>No Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a no malaria risk area</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B13S1.DE05<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B13S1.46DE05\"> </a></td><td>Less than 14 days</td><td>The client has had ear discharge for less than 14 days</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B13S1.DE06<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B13S1.46DE06\"> </a></td><td>14 days or more</td><td>The client has had ear discharge for 14 days or more</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">oxygen_saturation_above_90<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-oxygen_saturation_above_90\"> </a></td><td>Oxygen Saturation &gt;= 90 %</td><td>The client's oxygen saturation is more than or equal to 90 %</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B10S2.DE09<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B10S2.46DE09\"> </a></td><td>Oxygen Saturation &lt; 90 %</td><td>The client's oxygen saturation is less than 90 %</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B10S2.DE10<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B10S2.46DE10\"> </a></td><td>Oxygen saturation not measured</td><td>The clients oxygen saturation was not measured</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE05<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE05\"> </a></td><td>One Convulsion</td><td>The client is reported to have had one convulsion in this illness</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE06<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE06\"> </a></td><td>Two or more convulsions</td><td>The client is reported to have had two or more convulsions in this illness</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE11<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE11\"> </a></td><td>Vomiting Everything</td><td>The client is reported to be vomiting everything</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE12<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE12\"> </a></td><td>Vomiting but Not Everything</td><td>The client is reported to be vomiting but not vomiting everything</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE15<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE15\"> </a></td><td>Vomits immediately / everything</td><td>The client vomits immediately / everything</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE16<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE16\"> </a></td><td>Completely unable to drink</td><td>The client is completely unable to drink</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE17<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE17\"> </a></td><td>Drinks poorly</td><td>The client drinks poorly</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE18<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE18\"> </a></td><td>Drinks eagerly / thirstily</td><td>The client drinks eagerly / thirstily</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE19<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE19\"> </a></td><td>Drinks normally</td><td>The client drinks normally</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B7.DE20<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B7.46DE20\"> </a></td><td>Unable to perform test - assumes vomits everything/unable to drink</td><td>The health care worker is unable to perform test on the client therefore the health care worker should assume the client vomits everything or is unable to drink</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">fluid_test_passed<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-fluid_test_passed\"> </a></td><td>Successful</td><td>The client passes the fluid test</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B11S2.DE03<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B11S2.46DE03\"> </a></td><td>Skin Pinch Goes back Very slowly (More than 2 seconds)</td><td>The client's skin goes back very slowly after skin pinch of abdomen (More than 2 seconds)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B11S2.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B11S2.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>Skin Pinch Goes back Slowly (2 seconds or fewer, but not immediately)</td><td>The client's skin goes back slowly after skin pinch of abdomen (2 seconds or fewer, but not immediately)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B11S2.DE05<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B11S2.46DE05\"> </a></td><td>Goes back Normally (immediately)</td><td>The client's skin goes back normally after skin pinch of abdomen (immediately)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE19<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE19\"> </a></td><td>Skin Lesions ≥ 4 cm</td><td>The client has Skin Lesions ≥ 4 cm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE20<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE20\"> </a></td><td>Red Skin Streaks</td><td>The client has red skin streaks</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE21<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE21\"> </a></td><td>Tender Nodes (Nodules) under the skin</td><td>The client has tender nodes (nodules) under the skin that can appear on any part of the face or body</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE22<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE22\"> </a></td><td>Skin Infection extends to Muscle</td><td>The client has skin infection that extends to muscle</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE23<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE23\"> </a></td><td>Molluscum Contagiosum - Skin coloured pearly white papules with central umbilication. Most commonly seen on face and trunk in children.</td><td>The client has Molluscum Contagiosum - Skin coloured pearly white papules with central umbilication. Most commonly seen on face and trunk in children.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE24<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE24\"> </a></td><td>Warts - Papules or nodules with a rough (Verrucous) surface</td><td>The client has Warts - Papules or nodules with a rough (Verrucous) surface</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE25<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE25\"> </a></td><td>Seborrhea - Greasy scales and redness on central face and body folds</td><td>The client has Seborrhea - Greasy scales and redness on central face and body folds</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE26<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE26\"> </a></td><td>Fixed Drug Reactions - Generalised red, wide spread with small bumps or blisters; or one or more dark skin areas</td><td>The client has Fixed Drug Reactions - Generalised red, wide spread with small bumps or blisters; or one or more dark skin areas</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE27<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE27\"> </a></td><td>Eczema - Wet oozing sores or excoriated, thick patches</td><td>The client has Eczema - Wet oozing sores or excoriated, thick patches</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE28<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE28\"> </a></td><td>Steven Johnson Syndrome - Severe reaction due to cotrimoxazole or NVP involving the skin as well as the eyes and the mouth.  Might cause difficulty in breathing</td><td>The client has Steven Johnson Syndrome - Severe reaction due to cotrimoxazole or NVP involving the skin as well as the eyes and the mouth.  Might cause difficulty in breathing</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B13S2.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B13S2.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>Less than 14 days</td><td>The client has had pus draining from the ear for less than 14 days</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B13S2.DE05<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B13S2.46DE05\"> </a></td><td>14 days or more</td><td>The client has had pus draining from the ear for 14 days or more</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE06<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE06\"> </a></td><td>Generalised Skin Problem</td><td>The client has a generalised skin problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE07<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE07\"> </a></td><td>Localised Skin Problem</td><td>The client has a localised skin problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE10<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE10\"> </a></td><td>Possible Serious Abscess - Hot Tender Swelling</td><td>The client has a possible serious abscess - Hot tender swelling</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE11<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE11\"> </a></td><td>Cellulitis - Red Tender Skin</td><td>The client has Cellulitis - Red tender skin</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE12<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE12\"> </a></td><td>Papular Itching Rash(Prurigo) - Itching rash with small papules and scratch marks. Dark spots with pale centre</td><td>The client has Papular Itching Rash(Prurigo) - itching rash with small papules and scratch marks. Dark spots with pale centre</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE13<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE13\"> </a></td><td>Ringworm (Tinea) - An itchy circular lesion with a raised edge and fine scaly area in the centre with loss of hair.  May also be found on body or web on feet</td><td>The client has Ringworm (Tinea) - An itchy circular lesion with a raised edge and fine scaly area in the centre with loss of hair.  May also be found on body or web on feet</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE14<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE14\"> </a></td><td>Scabies - Rash and excoriations on torso; burrows in web space and wrists, face spared</td><td>The client has Scabies - Rash and excoriations on torso; burrows in web space and wrists, face spared</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE15<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE15\"> </a></td><td>Chickenpox - Vesicles over body.  Vesicles appear progressively over days and form scabs after they rupture</td><td>The client has Chickenpox - Vesicles over body.  Vesicles appear progressively over days and form scabs after they rupture</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE16<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE16\"> </a></td><td>Herpes Zoster -  Vesicles in one area on one side of body with intense pain or scars plus shooting pain.  Uncommon in children except where they are immuno-compromised (e.g. if infected with HIV)</td><td>The client has Herpes Zoster -  Vesicles in one area on one side of body with intense pain or scars plus shooting pain.  Uncommon in children except where they are immuno-compromised (e.g. if infected with HIV)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE17<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE17\"> </a></td><td>Impetigo / Folliculitis - Red, Tender, Warm Crusts or Small lesions</td><td>The client has Impetigo / Folliculitis - Red, Tender, Warm Crusts or Small lesions</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE32<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE32\"> </a></td><td>Oral Thrush</td><td>The client has oral thrush</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE33<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE33\"> </a></td><td>Mouth Sores or Mouth Ulcers - Deep and Extensive</td><td>The client has mouth sores or mouth ulcers that are deep and extensive</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE34<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE34\"> </a></td><td>Mouth Sores or Mouth Ulcers - Not Deep and Extensive</td><td>The client has mouth sores or mouth ulcers that are not deep and extensive</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE36<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE36\"> </a></td><td>Skin Problem</td><td>The health care worker would like to add a skin problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE37<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE37\"> </a></td><td>Oral Sores or Mouth Ulcers</td><td>The health care worker would like to add an Oral Sores or Mouth Ulcers problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B14S2.DE38<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B14S2.46DE38\"> </a></td><td>Eye Problem</td><td>The health care worker would like to add an Eye problem</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE01<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE01\"> </a></td><td>Palmar Pallor</td><td>The client has palmar pallor</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE03<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE03\"> </a></td><td>Some Palmar Pallor</td><td>The client has some palmar pallor</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE04<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE04\"> </a></td><td>No Palmar Pallor</td><td>The client has no palmar pallor</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE06<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE06\"> </a></td><td>High Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a high malaria risk area</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE07<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE07\"> </a></td><td>Low Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a low malaria risk area</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">EmCare.B15S2.DE08<a name=\"emc-custom-codes-codes-EmCare.46B15S2.46DE08\"> </a></td><td>No Malaria Risk</td><td>The client is in a no malaria risk area</td></tr></table></div>"
